# Sora 2 API — Complete Documentation & Feature Research

## Overview

OpenAI's Sora 2 offers AI video generation via two channels: the **web platform** (sora.com / ChatGPT) and the **developer API**. This document catalogs all known API endpoints, parameters, and compares web platform features to what's available via API.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> There are **two endpoint schemas** in use:
> - **Legacy / Azure-style**: `POST /v1/video/generations/jobs` ← *your current codebase uses this*
> - **Newer OpenAI native**: `POST /v1/videos` ← *newer official docs reference this*
> Both hit the same underlying model; the newer schema uses slightly different parameter names.

---

## 1. API Endpoints

### Core Endpoints (Legacy — `/v1/video/generations/jobs`)

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/v1/video/generations/jobs` | Create a video generation job |
| `GET` | `/v1/video/generations/jobs/{jobId}` | Poll job status |
| `GET` | `/v1/video/generations/{generationId}/content/video` | Download completed MP4 |

### Core Endpoints (Newer — `/v1/videos`)

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/v1/videos` | Create a video generation job |
| `GET` | `/v1/videos/{videoId}` | Get video status & metadata |
| `GET` | `/v1/videos/{videoId}/content` | Download video MP4 |
| `GET` | `/v1/videos?limit=N&after=ID&order=asc` | List all generated videos (paginated) |
| `DELETE` | `/v1/videos/{videoId}` | Delete a video from OpenAI storage |

> [!NOTE]
> **Your app currently uses**: the legacy 3-endpoint pattern. The newer API adds **List** and **Delete** endpoints plus slightly different parameter naming.

---

## 2. Create Video — Request Body Parameters

### Legacy Endpoint (`POST /v1/video/generations/jobs`)

Used by your current [server.js](file:///d:/SoraStudio/server.js). Accepts JSON or multipart/form-data.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| `model` | string | Yes | `"sora-2"` or `"sora-2-pro"` |
| `prompt` | string | Yes | Natural-language description of the video |
| `width` | integer | No | Output width in px (e.g. 1280) |
| `height` | integer | No | Output height in px (e.g. 720) |
| `n_seconds` | integer | No | Duration in seconds (5–20) |
| `n_variants` | integer | No | Number of variants to generate (1–4) |
| `inpaint_items` | JSON array | No | Image reference items for image-to-video (multipart only) |
| `files` | binary | No | Reference image file (multipart only) |

### Newer Endpoint (`POST /v1/videos`)

| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `prompt` | string | **Yes** | — | Detailed text prompt describing the video |
| `model` | string | No | `"sora-2"` | `"sora-2"` or `"sora-2-pro"` |
| `size` | string | No | `"1280x720"` | Resolution as `"WIDTHxHEIGHT"` string |
| `seconds` | integer | No | `4` | Duration: `4`, `8`, or `12` seconds |
| `input_reference` | file/URL | No | — | Reference image (JPEG/PNG/WebP). Dimensions must match `size` |
| `remix_id` | string | No | — | ID of existing video to remix/modify |
| `n` | integer | No | `1` | Number of video variants to generate |

---

## 3. Models

| Model | Quality | Max Resolution | Speed | Use Case |
|-------|---------|---------------|-------|----------|
| `sora-2` | Good | 720p (1280×720) | Fast | Rapid iteration, prototyping, social media |
| `sora-2-pro` | Production-grade | 1080p+ (1792×1024) | Slower | Cinematic footage, marketing assets |

---

## 4. Supported Resolutions

### sora-2

| Aspect Ratio | Resolutions |
|-------------|-------------|
| 16:9 (Landscape) | 854×480, 1280×720 |
| 9:16 (Portrait) | 480×854, 720×1280 |
| 1:1 (Square) | 480×480, 720×720 |

### sora-2-pro

| Aspect Ratio | Resolutions |
|-------------|-------------|
| 16:9 (Landscape) | 854×480, 1280×720, 1920×1080, 1792×1024 |
| 9:16 (Portrait) | 480×854, 720×1280, 1080×1920, 1024×1792 |
| 1:1 (Square) | 480×480, 720×720, 1080×1080 |

---

## 5. Job Status Values

```
queued → preprocessing → running → processing → succeeded
                                              → failed
                                              → cancelled
```

The job response includes:
- [id](file:///d:/SoraStudio/index.html#403-416) — Job ID
- `status` — One of the above values
- `generations[]` — Array of completed generations (each with its own [id](file:///d:/SoraStudio/index.html#403-416))
- `failure_reason` — Error message if `failed`

---

## 6. Web Platform Features vs API Availability

| Feature | Web Platform | API Available? | API Implementation |
|---------|-------------|----------------|-------------------|
| **Text-to-Video** | ✅ | ✅ | `prompt` parameter |
| **Image-to-Video** | ✅ | ✅ | `input_reference` / `inpaint_items` + file upload |
| **Remix** | ✅ | ✅ | `remix_id` parameter on create endpoint |
| **Storyboard** | ✅ | ⚠️ Partial | Not a single API call — requires chaining multiple generations with prompts per segment |
| **Blend** | ✅ | ❌ | Web-only experimental tool (combines two videos) |
| **Extend** | ✅ | ⚠️ Partial | Can be achieved via remix with continuation prompt |
| **Loop** | ✅ | ❌ | Web-only tool for seamless looping |
| **Re-cut** | ✅ | ❌ | Web-only trim/timing tool |
| **Synchronized Audio** | ✅ | ✅ | Generated automatically in Sora 2 output |
| **Characters / Cameo** | ✅ | ⚠️ Limited | Some API access to likeness injection (requires consent) |
| **Style Presets** | ✅ | ❌ | Web-only convenience — can be replicated via detailed prompts |
| **Remove Watermark** | Pro only | Pro only | Higher-tier access or `sora-2-pro` model |
| **C2PA Metadata** | ✅ | ✅ | Automatically embedded in all generated videos |
| **List Videos** | ✅ | ✅ | `GET /v1/videos` (newer API only) |
| **Delete Videos** | ✅ | ✅ | `DELETE /v1/videos/{id}` (newer API only) |

---

## 7. Image-to-Video (Input Reference) Details

When providing a reference image, the image acts as the first frame or visual guide:

- **Supported formats**: JPEG, PNG, WebP
- **Dimension requirement**: Image dimensions **must exactly match** the target video `size`
- **Max file size**: ~20 MB
- **Legacy API**: Uses multipart form-data with `inpaint_items` JSON array:
  ```json
  [
    {
      "frame_index": 0,
      "type": "image",
      "file_name": "reference.jpg",
      "crop_bounds": {
        "left_fraction": 0,
        "top_fraction": 0,
        "right_fraction": 1,
        "bottom_fraction": 1
      }
    }
  ]
  ```
- **Newer API**: Uses `input_reference` field directly (image URL or file upload)

---

## 8. Remix Feature

Remix lets you modify an existing video with a new prompt, keeping the base video's structure:

```json
{
  "model": "sora-2",
  "prompt": "Change the color of the car to red and add rain",
  "remix_id": "video_abc123",
  "seconds": 8,
  "size": "1280x720"
}
```

- Only available on newer `/v1/videos` endpoint
- Requires the `remix_id` of a previously generated video
- The prompt describes the desired modifications
- Supports varying "remix strength" on the web platform (not clearly exposed in API)

---

## 9. Authentication & Access

- **Auth header**: `Authorization: Bearer sk-...`
- **Organization verification required**: Must verify org at `platform.openai.com/settings/organization/general`
- **Access propagation**: Up to 15 minutes after verification
- **API access**: May require application/invite for preview access
- **Azure OpenAI**: Also available through Microsoft Foundry / Azure OpenAI service

---

