## 11. Example API Calls

### Text-to-Video (Newer API)
```bash
curl -X POST https://api.openai.com/v1/videos \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer sk-..." \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "sora-2",
    "prompt": "A cinematic shot of a golden retriever running through a field of sunflowers at sunset",
    "size": "1280x720",
    "seconds": 8
  }'
```

### Image-to-Video (Legacy API — your current approach)
```bash
curl -X POST https://api.openai.com/v1/video/generations/jobs \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer sk-..." \
  -F "model=sora-2" \
  -F "prompt=Animate this scene with gentle wind" \
  -F "width=1280" \
  -F "height=720" \
  -F "n_seconds=5" \
  -F "n_variants=1" \
  -F 'inpaint_items=[{"frame_index":0,"type":"image","file_name":"ref.jpg","crop_bounds":{"left_fraction":0,"top_fraction":0,"right_fraction":1,"bottom_fraction":1}}]' \
  -F "files=@ref.jpg"
```

### Remix (Newer API)
```bash
curl -X POST https://api.openai.com/v1/videos \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer sk-..." \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "sora-2",
    "prompt": "Make it nighttime with neon city lights",
    "remix_id": "video_abc123",
    "seconds": 8,
    "size": "1280x720"
  }'
```

### List Videos
```bash
curl "https://api.openai.com/v1/videos?limit=20&order=desc" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer sk-..."
```

### Delete Video
```bash
curl -X DELETE https://api.openai.com/v1/videos/video_abc123 \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer sk-..."
```

---

## 12. Pricing Notes

- **sora-2**: Lower cost per generation, suitable for iteration
- **sora-2-pro**: Higher cost, best for final production output
- Pricing scales with resolution, duration, and number of variants
- Free tier users: Limited generations per month at 480p
- Plus subscribers: ~50 videos/month at 720p
- Pro subscribers: Higher limits, 1080p, watermark-free downloads
- API pricing: Token/usage-based, varies by model
